# Mobile React Native Android Rules

## Intent
Standardize `packages/mobile` for React Native with Android production focus.

## Workflow Alignment
- Follow cloud-first build/update constraints from `expo-eas-mobile-workflow-rules.mdc`.

## Structure Rules
- Keep mobile-only UI in `packages/mobile/src/components` and `packages/mobile/src/screens`.
- Keep platform service wiring in `packages/mobile/src/services`.
- Keep native bridges/modules in `packages/mobile/src/native`.
- iOS project may exist for parity, but production release target is Android APK/AAB only.
- Keep architecture modular so high-load paths can be replaced with native modules without large rewrites.

## Performance Rules
- Use optimized list rendering patterns for chat timelines (`FlatList` tuning or equivalent virtualization strategy).
- Keep message row components lightweight and avoid expensive re-renders in long conversation threads.
- Apply throttling/debouncing and interval controls for realtime updates to protect JS thread performance.

## Security Rules
- Use secure OS-backed storage for tokens and sensitive session material.
- Do not emit PHI/PII to device logs, analytics payloads, or crash breadcrumbs.
- Use TLS pinning strategy and hardened networking in production builds.

## Release Rules
- GitHub Actions must produce signed Android release artifacts.
- Publish signed Android APK through GitHub Releases with changelog and build metadata.
- AAB is optional and may be published as a companion artifact, but APK is mandatory.
- Block Android release if lint/type/test/security/compliance gates fail.

## Prohibited
- Direct use of shared secrets in client source.
- Shipping debug logging in production flavor.